        "created_at": "2021-04-30T08:02:13.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>To celebrate a good friend\u2019s birthday , we were invited to a dinner with a lot of great wines . There were many outstanding wines such as VCC 1945 , Latour 82 ( delicious )and Haut Brion 1961 , but everybody\u2019s favorite was Haut Brion 1953 .<br>\nThe wine was dark in color with spices and tobacco on the nose , creamy blue fruit . Still fresh . I read old tasting notes from Parker ( in 93 and 94 ) that he suggests that the wine should be consumed over the near term . But this particular bottle is still going strong , almost 30 years later . Amazing</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
